HEADWORD: Chlorocruorin
<hw>Chlo`ro*cru"o*rin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>chlwro`s</grk> light green + E. <ets>cruorin</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>A green substance, supposed to be the cause
of the green color of the blood in some species of worms.</def>
<rj><au>Ray Lankester.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

